AAl-Nassr are on the hunt for more top players from Europe and have identified Real Madrid’s Eden Hazard as the next, after they landed Cristiano Ronaldo is a sensational transfer. Hazard has been linked with a move away from Spain for almost a year now. The Belgian’s career never really got off at the Santiago Bernabeu after he joined from Chelsea. According to Football Mercato, Al-Nassr are ready to capitalize. Al-Nassr manager, Rudi Garcia handed Hazard his debut at Lille and developed him into a promising young winger. Hazard’s contract with Real Madrid expires in 2024.